"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-06-parisolympics-bryan-levell-advances-repechage-200m-semis\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"National champion Bryan Levell took full advantage of a second chance as he qualified for the semi-finals of the men's 200m at the Olympic Games, advancing on time from the repechage round on Tuesday at Stade de France in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 23, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\", \"score\": 0.7850056996193511, \"rank\": 0.2738676340011423, \"text\": \"Bryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\"}, {\"begin\": 222, \"end\": 227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999979916736711, \"rank\": 2.0083666491412208e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Levell was second in his heat in 20.47 seconds (0.6m/s), behind Canada's Jamaica-based Brendon Rodney who ran 20.42 seconds and will hope to get into the final.\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 294, \"end\": 300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9876870264948477, \"rank\": 0.0046770868350250105, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 317, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brendon_Rodney\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brendon Rodney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brendon_Rodney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brendon_Rodney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the second Jamaican, Andrew Hudson failed to advance after he was caught a few steps from the finish line and passed by Sweden's Erik Erlandsson who ran a lifetime best 20.49 seconds (0.3m/s) to snatch the automatic qualifying spot.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 412, \"end\": 420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999894782207436, \"rank\": 7.03540406712172e-06, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 422, \"end\": 435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Hudson\", \"score\": 0.9999999998092335, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Hudson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Hudson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Hudson\"}, {\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9862713807647819, \"rank\": 0.010787708023036175, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hudson's 20.55 seconds was eighth best in the round with only six advancing.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"-Paul A Reid  Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": []}]}"